# Design Review Process and Checklist

This is very important to update and keep track of. Each year, we have design reviews with the competition (and other people like Professor Knox). Although the people in the team reguarly change (graduate, ...), those external stakeholders don't! 

Knowledge of those processes was lost in the past, we forgot things during design review, they call us out on the items we forget, and we looked very bad and like fools that didn't know what we do. So this is why **you must follow and update those processes**

**If you forget one item of those checklist, people will notice, and they will be mad at you because they already told us for 3 years to include those things, and you didn't read this document...**

> Let's follow this workflow, and be winners. Don't be a fool like I once was - Seb

## Steps

### Premilinary Design Review

Required Members: This steps involves the whole avionics team with airframe and captains

Must include:
- Previous experiences and what we want to change
- Overview of the goals of the SRAD system
- Overview of the way components will communicate together
- Possible candidates for arming
- What microprocessors will be used
- What communication system will be used
- Where is the avionics bay will be in the rocket
- Preliminary Power Budget
- What will be the major components

### Divide Tasks
Leads should know their team, and what are the strength of each member. Should use MS Planner to assign boards 

You should also
- Present deadlines to the team
- Use MS Planner
- Assign members with lower experience to future project, or side-projects



### Determine Pinout of Each Component
This is very important and simple. Don't skip this, otherwise you will regret!!

Make an **excel sheet** for each microprocessor and other important items that requires an IO that is controlled by software.

For each component, put on the excel sheet what pins will connect to what component. **Review those things with software**, **otherwise they will be mad at you**. That will allow:
 - Software can start testing those pins on breadboards with the component
 - Software has no excuse to change the pins later in the process, which will change your Schematics and PCB layout, and you will be mad at software too
 
### Work on Schematic

Work on stuff - get stuff done - work together

### Review each components with other members
As the lead, here must be an **independent review** for each component. **This person must not have work on the component in the past.** 

This means that for each hardware component, there must be someone that is qualified that looks at those thing
 - Pinout, will it work, does it match the excel pinout sheet, can we make it work with software
 - Power cunsumption of each component. 
 - Are you going to have a resistor that draws 30W and that will blow up
 - Are the example followed (for example, did you put capacitor on the crystal)
 - Are there debugging equipment (led, pins we can use to interract and flash the controller, ..)
